OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778119410
OL,3,CKeir Starmer faces judgment day as
OL,4,Cmillions head to polling stations
OL,6,FAn equally painful fate is expected
OL,7,Ffor Labour in Wales where the
OL,8,Fgoverning party is set to lose the
OL,9,Fnational vote for the first time in
OL,10,Fmore than a century.
OL,12,FThe Prime Minister has acknowledged
OL,13,Fthe elections will be "a challenge"
OL,14,Fbut in a final plea to voters he urged
OL,15,Fthem to "choose unity over division".
OL,17,FAlmost 25,000 candidates are fighting
OL,18,Fto be elected to more than 5,000 seats
OL,19,Fon 136 councils across England.
OL,26,@uD@WOUuD@cO]wD@IOUwD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
