OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778119410
OL,3,CKeir Starmer faces judgment day as
OL,4,Cmillions head to polling stations
OL,6,FShe added: "Under my leadership the
OL,7,FConservative Party has changed. We
OL,8,Fknow where we went wrong and we're
OL,9,Ffixing it.
OL,11,F"The next Conservative government will
OL,12,Fdeliver cheaper energy bills, take
OL,13,Fback our streets with 10,000 more
OL,14,Fpolice officers, cut business rates
OL,15,Ffor the high street, end the war on
OL,16,Fmotorists, and abolish stamp duty on
OL,17,Fthe family home."
OL,19,FMeanwhile, Liberal Democrat leader Sir
OL,20,FEd Davey is calling on voters to opt
OL,21,Ffor "hard-working local champions".
OL,26,@nD@LOUsD@AOUyD@QO]}D@EOU}D@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
