CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778119410
OL,3,CKeir Starmer faces judgment day as
OL,4,Cmillions head to polling stations
OL,6,F"Across the country, from Hampshire to
OL,7,FHull, the battle is now between the
OL,8,FLiberal Democrats and Reform. We are
OL,9,Fthe ones taking the fight to them and
OL,10,Fstanding up for decency, tolerance and
OL,11,Fthe rule of law.
OL,13,FIn his final message, Reform UK leader
OL,14,FNigel Farage hit out at Sir Keir,
OL,15,Fbranding him "gutless" and accused the
OL,16,FTories of failing to remove the
OL,17,F"unpatriotic" Prime Minister.
OL,19,FHe added: "Together, we can continue
OL,20,Fthe journey of getting our great
OL,21,Fcountry back on track.
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@NOUwD@VO]yD@AOUyD@MO]{D@KOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
