OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778119410
OL,3,CKeir Starmer faces judgment day as
OL,4,Cmillions head to polling stations
OL,6,FCabinet ministers are not said to be
OL,7,Famong those committed to signing the
OL,8,Fletter, although there are rumblings
OL,9,Fof a potential leadership tilt by
OL,10,FHealth Secretary Wes Streeting, former
OL,11,Fdeputy prime minister Angela Rayner or
OL,12,FGreater Manchester Mayor Andy Burnham.
OL,14,FUnions will also be looking to topple
OL,15,FSir Keir as leader, according to the
OL,16,FTelegraph, with an anonymous source
OL,17,Ftelling the newspaper: "The change and
OL,18,Fprogress that was promised before the
OL,19,Fgeneral election just hasn't
OL,20,Fmaterialised."
OL,26,@yD@XOU|D@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/14
