OL,3,CKeir Starmer faces judgment day as
OL,4,Cmillions head to polling stations
OL,6,FWork and Pensions Secretary Pat
OL,7,FMcFadden insisted on Wednesday that
OL,8,FSir Keir was in a "resolute" mood and
OL,9,Ftriggering a leadership contest would
OL,10,Fbe a mistake.
OL,12,FLabour Party deputy leader Lucy Powell
OL,13,Fsignalled her support for Sir Keir on
OL,14,Fthe eve of the elections but
OL,15,Fsidestepped questions about whether he
OL,16,Fshould lead the party into the next
OL,17,Fgeneral election.
OL,26,@pD@SOUpD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/14
